This paper deals with natural language processing and knowledge representation, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on mapping text to knowledge graph entities also relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
